race.comment: NEWCOMBE (16) was narrowly beaten at Kyneton and Sale this distance range and resumed 11 days ago at Sale with a decent effort over 1427m. Has a wide gate but will relish the step up to the mile and has plenty up his sleeve. LUCKY DIAMOND (15) finished alongside the above in that contest coming with a strong run from well back. He will have to do it the hard way again, but this is an ideal next step. CUBAN DAWN (1) has been freshened and comes back from middle distances. Has been kept up to the mark with a jumpout placing at Mornington and has run his best races on turf over this distance. Should be around the mark. NIKEPHOROS (4) will position forward from the inside barrier and won't be far away forgiving his latest.
